name: Cecil HOLMES, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, PA., Respondent
name_abbreviation: Holmes v. Court of Common Pleas

parties: Cecil HOLMES, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, PA., Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 31st day of July, 2013, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED. To the extent the Petition for Writ of Mandamus and/or Extraordinary Relief requests extraordinary relief, it is DENIED. To the extent the Petition for Writ of Mandamus and/or Extraordinary Relief requests mandamus relief, it is GRANTED. The Court of Common Pleas of Philadelphia County is directed to dispose of Petitioner’s pending petition for writ of habeas corpus within 90 days of this order.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.
